(secondQuint)A Comparison of Methylphenidate and Cognitive Behavioural Therapy for the Treatment of Binge Eating Disorder.

 Fifty-six adult female outpatients with binge eating disorder will receive 12 weeks of methylphenidate (dosage 18-72 mg) or 12 sessions of manualized cognitive behavioral therapy.

 Participants will complete interviewer-rated and self-report measures of eating, mood, attention, and personality features before treatment, after 6 weeks of treatment, immediately after treatment is completed, and 3 months after treatment is completed.

